# tRPC v11

All type-safe application APIs live in `packages/api`. Web app calls them via a typed client; never reach into Prisma from React components.

## Package Layout (`packages/api`)

```text
packages/api/src/
  trpc.ts          # initTRPC + context + procedure helpers
  root.ts          # appRouter composition; export type AppRouter
  routers/
    wedding.ts     # feature routers
  index.ts         # re-exports appRouter, AppRouter type, createContext
```

## Router Setup

```ts
// packages/api/src/trpc.ts
import { initTRPC } from "@trpc/server";
import superjson from "superjson";

export const createTRPCContext = async () => ({ /* request-scoped deps */ });

const t = initTRPC.context<Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createTRPCContext>>>().create({
  transformer: superjson,
});

export const router = t.router;
export const publicProcedure = t.procedure;
```

```ts
// packages/api/src/routers/wedding.ts
import { z } from "zod";
import { getPrisma } from "@darchive/db";
import { router, publicProcedure } from "../trpc";

export const weddingRouter = router({
  guestbookList: publicProcedure.query(() => getPrisma().weddingGuestbookEntry.findMany({
    where: { isVisible: true },
    orderBy: { createdAt: "desc" },
    take: 30,
    select: { id: true, name: true, message: true, createdAt: true },
  })),
  guestbookCreate: publicProcedure
    .input(z.object({ name: z.string().max(40), message: z.string().max(500) }))
    .mutation(({ input }) => getPrisma().weddingGuestbookEntry.create({
      data: input,
      select: { id: true, name: true, message: true, createdAt: true },
    })),
});
```

## Next.js App Router Handler

```ts
// apps/web/src/app/api/trpc/[trpc]/route.ts
import { fetchRequestHandler } from "@trpc/server/adapters/fetch";
import { appRouter, createTRPCContext } from "@darchive/api";

const handler = (req: Request) =>
  fetchRequestHandler({ endpoint: "/api/trpc", req, router: appRouter, createContext: createTRPCContext });

export { handler as GET, handler as POST };
```

## Client (React Query Integration)

- Use `@trpc/react-query` `createTRPCReact<AppRouter>()` and provide a `TRPCProvider` next to `QueryClientProvider`.
- Call procedures via hooks: `trpc.wedding.guestbookList.useQuery()` / `.useMutation()`.
- Validate inputs with Zod inside `.input(...)` — never trust the client.
- Throw `TRPCError` (e.g. `new TRPCError({ code: "BAD_REQUEST", message: "..." })`) for typed errors.

## Rules

- New backend endpoints must be tRPC procedures, not raw `app/api/*/route.ts` handlers (the trpc fetch handler is the only `route.ts` allowed for app APIs).
- Keep procedure files small and feature-scoped under `routers/`.
- Export only `AppRouter` **type** to the web app — never the runtime router instance.
- Reuse Zod input schemas between server (`.input`) and client forms.
